Cataract:

• Cataract is a condition in which the clarity of the natural lens reduces
• Lens of the eye becomes opaque
• This hampers the passage of light leading to drastic vision loss

Symptoms to look for:

• Blurred vision
• Inability to focus on objects
• Double vision
• Dark spots
• Vision is better in twilight
• Gradual loss of vision
• In later stages, objects are seen as mere blobs of light
• Greyish white discolouration of the pupil
• Glare in sunlight or while driving at night because of headlights

Causes:

• Ageing
• Exposure to excessive UV rays
• Smoking
• Diabetes

